GitHub Pages
From your project repo (I highly recommending creating a separate repo for your project and not using the class repo) click on settings. 


Next click on launch automatic page generator. 


Update the markdown. A few notes here…. 

1) You should upload all of your images to your github repo to make it easy to include in your page.
2) ? is an example of an image. Note the ?raw=True at the end
3) Check mark is an example of a title. Same as jupiter notebook # is big title. ### is smaller title
4) Heart is an example of a link


1) ! is an example of a inline link where Kiva blog post is a hyper link within the sentence .
2) X is an example of an unordered list. You can do this using *
3) Once your done with your markup click on continue to layouts. (check mark)

1) Choose your theme (?)
2) Hit publish (Check mark)
3) You’re done!!!
